    <caption><emphasis effect="bold">The musk gland of the male Himalayan musk deer secretes a substance once used in perfumery that contains cycloalkanes of 14 to 18 carbons</emphasis>. (credit: modification of work “Siberian musk deer in the tiaga” by ErikAdamsson/Wikimedia Commons, CC0 1.0)</caption>
